Share

If your tests are flaky, slow, or constantly failing after “harmless” refactors, it’s usually not bad luck — it’s bad testing habits. Here are the **biggest gotchas** developers run into with **React Testing Library (RTL)** and **Vitest**, with **clear DOs/DON’Ts** and copy-pasteable examples.

